Q17: The Aetna Breast and Ovarian Cancer Susceptibility Gene Testing Prior Authorization Form must be completed by the provider, confirming the basis for high-risk status. This form, along with the Laboratory's Test Requisition Form, should be submitted to Aetna for precertification. Documentation of specific cancer diagnosis in the proband(s) and pertinent medical records may be required prior to authorization. A summary indicating how this testing will change the immediate medical care of the member must also be included with the Prior Authorization request.
